caption: Super crowded but I'm thinking that's a good thing lol Opposite wouldn't be fun!
Kind of loud, but that's probably it's thing.  It was really busy later at night, so it seems to be a place where people enjoy hanging out.
Awesome place

Walked in at 12:40 to grab a quick beer and by 12:50 this lady was screaming kicking everyone out. This was my first time at the bar and she made me not want to come back. I thought I found a new neighborhood bar that I would be able to go to but I guess not.

Small and chill bar, very very very low-key. Drinks are strong and not expensive. Free popcorn is definitely a plus! A great place if you just want to unwind without much commotion, although you could do that at home too. Not likely to go back because that's not my type of bar, but if you're looking for something small and low-key, go for it.

Wow. What a total disappointment. Wabash Tap was recommended as a good "dive bar" which is what I was expecting. What I didn't expect was the one bartender doing pours halfway into the glass and halfway into the drain because he didn't know how to pour beer without giving you a glass full of head. While there was a good selection the beer was lukewarm at best which completely ruined it for me. No one expects warm beer from the tap and if you can't do a clean pour you shouldn't be behind the bar. I can only imagine how much income is wasted by these pours. Thank you, next.
3 1/2 stars

We love this place! We've been going to Helmand since they were in their former location on Broadway. Food is great, price is right, service is excellent. As vegetarians, we love their non-meat options. Highly recommended.
I really liked the paints as a art work on the walls, and a wall paper with the picture of city of Helmand.
Pool table. Decent beer. Good price.
Great local bat with friendly customers and staff. If Patrick is working you're in good hands.
Rebuilding, welcoming enough, trying to find itself

Although, I haven't been there in a hot minute, I love this place.  Great neighborhood bar with great bar fare.  Every time I am there the bartenders are attentive -- especially Jill -- she's the best.

One night when I came here the bartender (and only worker) was passed out at the bar. One plus is, if the bartender's awake, you won't be fighting for attention since this place is pretty consistently empty
It's ok staff could be more accommodating, but not bad.

The bartender (fat guy with a constant mean face) gave the worst service ever.  I asked nicely to turn down the lights and when he acknowledge me he was very condescending.  I asked another bartender to turn down the lights and she did immediately. After a few mins the bartender I  asked the first time turned the lights even brighter than it was previously so we decided to close out and never come back again. Who does that?!?!? Extremely rude service and an even more terrible person. Ive been going there for years and will never go again, sadly. They should've kept Jill. That fat mean muggin bartender should not be in the SERVICE Industry. He's a joke. Complete joke of a person. The other bartender was very friendly and seemed very uncomfortable even sharing the same space with him. I feel for her.  I wish her and the doorman the best of luck. It's a shame one person had to ruin the Tap. Cheers to the old times though, it used to a great bar.
Great place to drink and watch the game.. with free popcorn
I only gave 3 stars cause well, it's a bar. Nothing great. Now when they had food, I'd give them 5 stars. What happened Wabash?
the blue hair bartender rules
Nice place,  cheap  happy hour.
I’ve been here a few times. Nothing wrong with the place, just not my fave. Solid selections of beers and good staff. Can’t go wrong here.
Cold beer. Great air conditioning on a hot day!!
Good games and reasonably priced
The bartenders make Wabash Tap a great spot. The drinks are right and the crowd is a great for us 25-30 something loaners of Chicago or the wandering couple.
Good sports bar.

Love this place! I go here with my work friends all the time. Usually some good stuff in draft. Reasonable pricing makes for a good night. Also there's a popcorn machine and you can serve yourself which is great when you're need to eat something while tipsy.
Great bar atmosphere and great bar tenders! Highly recommend for anyone passing through or locals
best south loop bar.   Good pint of Guinness with decent pool tables.   Great food as well!
Decent bar, fair price for a beer and a shot
Cheap drinks
Quiet
Very low-key bar with two pool tables, darts, and popcorn machine. Bartender had always been quick and welcoming.
The tall waitress was extremely rude
Nice little place. Too bad no Guinness flowing on St Patty's day.
Goto spot when we're in South loop for cheap beer and free popcorn.

This has been our local late night go-to for about a year now, but we’ll never go back after tonight. One guy decided to spend the evening continuously walking past our group trying to pick a fight and agitate us for no reason. The bartender just stood there and watched, and only finally intervened once he overheard the guy racially abuse one of our group. By that point we were already on our way out. The guy kept harassing us all the way to the front door and the staff including the bouncer just stood there and did nothing. Amazing what a small-time dive bar will do to keep their douche-bag regulars happy!
Craft beers at a decent price.
Bad service. Really rude staff. This place is not worth visiting.

I have never in my entire life had a worst experience at a bar, in any country I've been to. We arrived about an hour before closing time, and sat down with a beer. The staff seemed friendly and nice, but after about 15 minutes they told us we had to leave because they were closing. We asked for a bit more time to be able to finish the drinks we just started on,  and the bouncer was already then starting to act really rude. He came back after five minutes, and started to threaten us to leave. When we stood up to put on our jackets, he told us he would call the police if we didn't get out at once. This was 20 minutes prior to closing time, and some people were still coming in at the same time. The bartender was also really rude and also threatened us. STAY AWAY!
Typical neighborhood bar. Drinks are decently priced. They have darts and pool tables. Great local place.
Trash

As far as dive bars go, I loved this place. The bartenders were friendly, the drinks were strong and reasonably prices, and they have free popcorn while you play pool or darts. Met some awesome locals here too.
Best dive in the South Loop. Good prices, friendly bartenders, and always good vibes
Beer and popcorn.
Nice atmosphere....locals hangout.

Let me just say that Jessica, Mike, and the remainder of the staff did a phenomenal job of taking care of my friends and I last Saturday.  I spoke with Jessica a week before and told her I would like to host my birthday get together at Wabash Tap but was hesitant because of the Gluten free beer selection. She ordered another type from her distributor before this past Saturday and the staff went above and beyond to meet that need along with offered a few more perks like reserved section and help with  music. Everyone had a great time and I definitely found my new hangout for around that area.  I'll be going back for sure. If you're looking for a great dive bar in the South loop, this one is #1 in my opinion. Give the place a try if you have not.  Thanks for reading.
Great local bar. Wednesdays and Thursdays are best.
Small, chill, 2 am bar near Roosevelt collection. Best attribute is the FREE popcorn machine! 2 pool tables, darts, a couple t.v's and friendly staff.
Nice spot to have cold beer and relax
Nice and quiet for a Sunday afternoon. Good location, within walking distance of red line and soldier field. Definitely the kind of place to make myself a regular visitor..
They need to bring the tots back
It's like a cool old man bar...only it's clientele is sketchy and it's not very cool. Limited beer selection.
Not bad, but not good. Kinda grody and has an unfinished feel that makes it feel more like a bar at a bowling alley, however the drinks were fine and the service was attentive.
Divy/brosy bar. Great location. Excellent bartenders
Cheap price.frirndly staff
Fairly cheap drinks and free popcorn. What else do you need?
Good place, good people, inexpensive,  Happy Hour!
Great place to have a drink
They stopped serving food, but still a decent bar with cheap beers
Good price for location generally not the southloops finest
Cheap drinks
Great bar, awesome service. Real good burgers.

I just love this place, as evidenced by how I stay hours longer and get way drunker than planned every time I go! The environment is no-frills, but there is touch tunes, pool tables, good food, and space at the bar- everything my husband and I look for in a bar! It's not like anything else in the neighborhood.
I love this place it feels like "cheers" it's a place you can go and just relax with a few good drinks.!! The food is SO GOOD.!!! Christian is a good cook.! The food and drinks are awesome
Nice beer selection
Straight forward bar in the South Loop. Top spot to watch a Bears game or visit before walking to Soldier Field
Low key, easy going, with a neighborhood vibe. Pool tables & darts

I wait tables around the corner at the Giordano's in the South Loop. I stop by the Tap  on stressful nights, and no matter how busy she is, Jill always takes care of me and listens to me vent. Give the girl a raise. She deserves it! Thanks for always taking care of my needs Jill!!!
I love the atmosphere and the beer selection. Eats are great, too. Jill and Eddie make this place feel like Cheers! One o fd the best casual sports bars in town!
Meh. Not terrible, not great.
it is a bar...

Looking for a VERY relaxed place to meet up for a drink? This is perfect. There's a little patio in front where you can people watch too. Food isn't GREAT but you can watch them make it if you sit at the bar so... it's kinda dinner and a show?
Nice bar. Friendly staff. Good Guiness. Nice patrons
Very friendly atmosphere
Easy going. Opposite of a place for downtown traders and business d-bags. Good prices, good experience.  Lots of TVs.
Nice people...Good beer!!
Pool table in the back. Order a shot of malort if you are just visiting for the night.
Love this place so many good memories there.
Cool little neighborhood bar and cheap drinks
Best hole-in-the-wall bar
$3 Anti Heroes during happy hour. Need I say more.  The posts about them being racist is a joke. Diverse crowd and nothing but great service!  New favorite place in walking distance.
Nice little dive bar, heavy pours and cheap drinks what more could you ask for. 2 pool tables

In a neighborhood full of trendy joints, Wabash Tap (formerly Koko Taylor's Celebrity club) is a pleasant blue collar bar perfect for a pub lunch or a nice place to get together with workmates for that after work drink. Low key and intimate, Wabash Tap is a welcome respite and one of the last examples of enduring Chicago culture in the South Loop
Great wings and friendly atmosphere.
So-so drink selection, very basic pub food, standard bar environment

I would never in life attend this bar. The bartender and manager was very racist and disrespectful. I didn't know the bartender's name. So I said hey maam....she was rude and ignored me. I proceeded to get her attention again. She replied you wont get any service like that. I asked for a manager and when he came I explained the situation. He was just as rude as she was. I left and took my money to the scout. Wabash Tap was rude, racist and very unprofessional. I wouldn't recommend taking a dog to the establishment. Let alone any human being. Especially if you're a Black American.
Dive bar in the cusp of the south loop, pool and small patio seating in front. No frills, come here for a cold one.
Set your expectations low and get blown away with having a good time.
Xoxo
Perfect dive bar. Go during Happy Hour
Why does it say the bar is closed on Saturday? One look at the website shows it is open Saturday. What bar is closed Saturday?
Nice chill place for a beer or a shot. Pool tables, popcorn, etc. Nothing fancy, but that's a good thing in this case.
Bartenders seem a little clueless. I'd sit with an empty glass waiting for a refill for way too long. Food is mediocre, but a value at the price. Two dart boards and a pool table.
Great neighborhood bar. Even as an out of towner, I was welcomed.
Place was packed both times I visited. Not bad beer prices and good laid back atmosphere. Bartenders seemed nice enough to me.
Seems like a nice place. Rock n roll playing on the box, darts and pool! A normal like back home bar!
Laid back sports bar in the South loop with solid food and good beer selection. They have darts!

Had our work holiday party here this year - great location for a small group. Typical bar food and an average selection of drinks. Just off the red line, an okay place to stop if you're just looking to have a beer.

We were heading to a Bears night game and we wanted to grab a few affordable beers before seeing da Bears. I did a search of the neighborhood on line and found this location.  I wasn't the only one because this place was packed. Beer price were very affordable plus they sold pitchers too. I don't know of any place in the city that still sells pitchers.  The bartenders were fast and efficient even though they were slammed full of people going to the game. After seeing the Bears win we headed back here for a victory beer and it was still packed but we managed to grab a table. We were just winning all around.

Wabash Tap is an OK dive bar in the South Loop. There's pool tables for entertainment  and a decent selection of beer. Honestly the food really fell flat. The popcorn and tots are a nice touch but there's better burgers (bar and otherwise) in the area to choose from and I'd have to choose those in a minute.  Honestly if you were looking to spend a few hours at a bar this wouldn't be at the top of my list but if you are doing a mini crawl or hopping between the two - stopping in for an hour would be fine.

I love the food at htis place.  IT is simple and awesome.  The tater tots are very good and come with different types of sauces to use for dipping.  I come here pretty often for a beer and some tots and always have left happy.
A bit of a whole in the wall, but every hood needs one.  Decent beer selection, food is okay, but more of a meetup place.
awesome

Came here Friday night with some friends. Sat at a table and they made me give them my credit card. When leaving, we paid cash for our tab and I forgot my credit card at the bar. Realized that my card was at the bar today and checked my statement; Sure enough they ran my card for the amount on the tab we paid cash for. Had the pleasant experience this afternoon of dealing with a very rude woman when trying to work out the situation. They say they have no record of our tab being paid and will not credit the amount on my card. Will never go to this place again. Only good thing about it is there is a ping pong table and free popcorn.
Service/attitude very meh, and prices a bit inflated, given the unsophisticated crowd. Lots of 'bros' in there.
Great place to relax.  They have a nice selection of tasty beers.  Also make sure you get the TOTs here with the dipping sauces.  The other food is decent bar food.
A nice beer selection (especially for a "dive bar"), great specials, and excellent tater tots!
